# Publish and IIS Deploy Conventions

Full docs: `C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth\docs\integration\publish-and-deploy-guide.md`

## Publish Profiles (.pubxml)

- `WebApp-FileSystem.pubxml` -- ASP.NET Core web apps (IIS-hosted)
- `WinApp-FileSystem.pubxml` -- background services / console apps
- Always set BOTH `PublishUrl` and `PublishDir` to the same UNC path (VS uses one, CLI uses the other)

## Publish Destination Paths

Target: `C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\DedgeWinApps\<name>`

- **Single-project solutions**: folder = solution name (e.g. `\DedgeAuth`, `\DocView`)
- **Multi-project solutions**: folder = `<Solution>-<Component>` (e.g. `\GenericLogHandler-WebApi`, `\GenericLogHandler-ImportService`)

Each component gets its own isolated folder -- no shared parent, no DLL collisions.

## IIS Deploy Templates

Location: `IIS-DeployApp\templates\<SiteName>_<InstallSource>.deploy.json`

Critical path alignment rule:
- `InstallAppName` must match the folder name on the DedgeCommon share
- `PhysicalPath` must resolve to the same folder after `Install-OurWinApp` copies it locally
- For multi-project: `InstallAppName` includes component suffix (e.g. `GenericLogHandler-WebApi`), but `SiteName`/`VirtualPath` use solution name only

## Build Script Pattern

```powershell
dotnet publish $projectPath /p:PublishProfile=WebApp-FileSystem -v minimal
```

The profile handles configuration, runtime, output path, and self-contained mode.

## After Changing IIS-DeployApp Files

Always run `.\IIS-DeployApp\_deploy.ps1` to sync updated scripts/templates to servers.

## Code Signing

All `.csproj` files must include DedgeSign targets for Release builds. See `setup-guide.md` Step 8.
